    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Fever Meme is a comedy/parody game that pivots between multiple genres as it spits in the face of traditional game design. <br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3110070/extras/76573acb5015a1554b89c2a4e5af0434.poster.avif?t=1764329811\" width=616 height=240 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3110070/extras/76573acb5015a1554b89c2a4e5af0434.webm?t=1764329811\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3110070/extras/76573acb5015a1554b89c2a4e5af0434.mp4?t=1764329811\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span>One moment you'll be in a 2007-esque rage platformer, the next moment you'll be in the game show with a giant spider. But beneath all of the trolls and humor is a deeper overarching story. The game is self-aware of your actions as you play, your past mistakes, and so much more. And the further you make it into the game, the more the dynamic between player and creator is explored as the fourth wall is completely stripped away.<br><br><strong>DISCLAIMER: Do not play if you are prone to photosensitive epilepsy or are sensitive to loud audio.</strong></p>",
